**End-to-end UX flow (who does what)**
1. User signs in on landing page -> [src/app/page.tsx](/C:/Users/pracu/OneDrive/Desktop/2026/Orkestrate/src/app/page.tsx).  
2. Callback exchanges code and creates/ensures active workspace -> [src/app/auth/callback/route.ts](/C:/Users/pracu/OneDrive/Desktop/2026/Orkestrate/src/app/auth/callback/route.ts), [src/lib/workspaces-core.ts](/C:/Users/pracu/OneDrive/Desktop/2026/Orkestrate/src/lib/workspaces-core.ts).  
3. Dashboard/workspace UI uses workspace API -> [src/pages/api/workspaces.ts](/C:/Users/pracu/OneDrive/Desktop/2026/Orkestrate/src/pages/api/workspaces.ts).  
4. MCP client is configured/authenticated from docs/setup UI -> [src/components/ClientSetup.tsx](/C:/Users/pracu/OneDrive/Desktop/2026/Orkestrate/src/components/ClientSetup.tsx), [src/app/docs/page.tsx](/C:/Users/pracu/OneDrive/Desktop/2026/Orkestrate/src/app/docs/page.tsx).  
5. MCP OAuth handshake runs through OAuth endpoints -> `authorize -> token -> mcp`, and MCP binds agent actions to user’s active workspace.  

